      <title>Re: Weekly Question? Why bother?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=235616#M235616</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A good number of the weekly questions have come directly to me, since the queries tend to be related to&amp;nbsp;the spell system&amp;nbsp;that I've recently been handed the keys to.&amp;nbsp; I'm not going to have a solid answer for any of them yet, and I'd rather give out a real answer later when I have a firm grasp on the system and what I want to do with it instead of an "I'll look into it" now, but since there's a need for feedback:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Q: Our class has utility spell X and the recast time makes it inconvenient to use.&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A: I'm all in favor of changing spells that are inconvenient simply for the sake of being inconvenient, but if it a change would allow you to gain aggro faster, absorb damage faster, cure counters faster, heal damage faster, or kill mobs faster... then there's going to be&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;shift in power, and the end result of the change&amp;nbsp;would need to be considered carefully.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Q: My&amp;nbsp;Prophecy of Ro spell&amp;nbsp;Y leaves something to be desired...&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A: I'd like to evaluate the PoR spells and improve the ones that aren't worth using.&amp;nbsp; I can't give a firm time on when this will be completed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Q: My class would like to see an&amp;nbsp;upgrade to&amp;nbsp;spell line Z.&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A: Thank you for the feedback.&amp;nbsp; I'll keep that in mind when&amp;nbsp;planning&amp;nbsp;spell upgrades for the next time the level cap is increased.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
