&lt;P&gt;The other thing to keep in mind is that weekly question does NOT necessarily mean, imply, or infer "weekly answer".&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sometimes we'll get an answer, and sometimes we won't.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Most questions that have shown up have been Spell, AA, or Item related... or just too general to get an appropriate answer.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; In some of these cases, our answer will sometimes be delayed sometimes even indefinitely.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; One of the issues that arises is when expectations are that every class will have the answer to their question every week... the same basic thing happenned with the top 10 lists.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;We'll continue to ask questions, but we will not always get answers, and as long as folks understand that, then they'll be much less prone to unreasonable disappointment.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
